title: Match History Problem
body: On the league website, when I go to check my match history(from the little profile drop-down menu) the page loads, but displays everything blank, with no matches appearing. I've tried reloading the page, relogging into my account, and using a different browser. I can still check my match history in the actual client, but not on the website.

replies.body: It's also an issue for me, browser cache cleared, everything. I also tried it with a newly installed browser, installed just to check my match history or match history of the world's games, still no dice.

There's a known bug with the website that happens occasionally that causes this to happen. Sometimes it can be resolved by [clearing your browser's cache](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752694-Clearing-Browser-History-and-Cookies) or by disabling all add-ons (if applicable).

Let me know if you have any questions.
Clearing my cache for the past day didn't fix it. I am unable to turn off all my add-ons for the browser(firefox). Is there anything else I can do?
Try another browser without addons and let me know if you still experience this.

That's happening also to me and it's super annoying, can't even see the world's match history :\ I've with two browsers without addons and clearing the caches  but with no results, is there no other way to fix this bug?
